canonical:
  title: 謝表
  author: 金富儀
  language: lzh
  text: 生育之勤有懷於是日撫存之寵不替於常年仰戴慈憐豈勝感勵中謝 伏惟皇帝紹先王之業豐茂世之規威惠並行式乃九圍之命謙恭不伐得其萬國之心故雖藩服之微不閒皇明之燭特紆膚使俯記生辰豈唯慰藉之溫言亦有匪頒之異數施非求報空慙上聖之恩遠而不忘誓竭外臣之節
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝表
  author: 金富儀
  language: lzh
  text: 生育之勤。有懷於是日。撫存之寵。不替於常年。仰戴慈憐。豈勝感勵。中謝。 伏惟皇帝。紹先王之業。豐茂世之規。威惠並行。式乃九圍之命。謙恭不伐。得其萬國之心。故雖藩服之微。不閒皇明之燭。特紆膚使。俯記生辰。豈唯慰藉之溫言。亦有匪頒之異數。施非求報。空慙上聖之恩。遠而不忘。誓竭外臣之節。
korean:
  title: 사표
  author: 김부의
  language: kor
  text: |-
    낳고 기른 부지런을 이날에 생각하며 어루만지시고 염려해 주시는 은총이 해마다 변치 않사오니, 우러러 사랑으로 어여뻐해 주시는 은총을 받자옴에 어찌 감려(感勵)를 이기오리이까. 중사(中謝)
    엎드려 생각하옵건대, 황제께옵서 선왕(先王)의 업을 이으시고 성대(盛代)의 규모를 풍성케 하시어 위엄과 은혜가 아울러 행하시니, 이는 곧 하늘의 명을 받아 구위(九圍 구주(九州))에 법을 보임이요, 겸양하고 공손하여 자랑하지 않음으로 만국의 인심을 얻으심이로소이다. 그러므로 비록 번복(藩服)의 미신(微臣)에게도 환하게 비추심이 간격이 없으시어 특별히 친사(親使)를 보내셔서 굽어 생신을 기억해 주시고 위자(慰藉)하시는 따뜻한 말씀뿐 아니라 또한 이수(異數)의 반사품(頒賜品)까지 내리시오니, 베푸심이 보수를 구함이 아니온지라, 한갓 상성(上聖)의 은혜를 부끄러워하오며, 오래도록 잊지 않아 맹세코 외신(外臣)의 절개를 다하겠나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0380_010_0150&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Memorial of Gratitude
  author: Kim Bu-ui
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your nurturing care through all my days—I hold this remembrance close on this auspicious occasion. The tenderness of your regard does not fade with the turning years. When I gaze upon such mercy and affection, how can my heart contain such overwhelming gratitude?

    —A respectful interlude—

    I humbly reflect: Your Majesty inherits the great work of former kings and expands the glory of this illustrious age. With both authority and compassion you govern, establishing the mandate of heaven across the nine provinces. Through humility and reverence, without boastfulness, you have won the hearts of all nations. Thus even to one so humble as a distant minister in your realm, your radiant attention shines without interruption. You have graciously sent your own messenger to remember and honor my birthday—not merely with warm words of comfort, but with extraordinary tokens of your regard. Though your benevolence seeks no return, I can only stand ashamed before such supreme kindness. Yet I vow never to forget, and pledge myself utterly to the loyalty befitting a distant subject of the throne.
  footnotes:
    - This is a formal memorial of thanks (謝表), a literary genre common in East Asian court tradition, typically offered by a provincial official or family member upon receiving imperial favor or recognition.
    - The 'interlude' marks a formal division in the memorial's structure, moving from personal gratitude to broader considerations of imperial virtue and cosmic order.
    - The 'nine provinces' refers to the traditional Chinese conception of the empire's territorial extent and administrative organization.
